fields.class_description: Safe-class SCPs are anomalies that are easily and safely contained.
Euclid-class SCPs are anomalies that require more resources to contain completely or where containment isn't always reliable.
Keter-class SCPs are anomalies that are exceedingly difficult to contain consistently or reliably, with containment procedures often being extensive and complex.
Thaumiel-class SCPs are anomalies that the Foundation uses to contain or counteract other SCPs or anomalous phenomena.
Used for SCPs that are impossible to contain, or are about to irrevocably break containment. An SCP with this class will inevitably end the world.
